    <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
      <head>Biographical Note</head>
      <p>Irish poet Derek Mahon met <persname authfilenumber="9071711" source="viaf">Louis
          Asekoff</persname> in the early 1960s while they were students at <corpname
          authfilenumber="Trinity_College,_Dublin" source="dbpedia">Trinity College</corpname> in
          <geogname authfilenumber="2964574" source="geonames">Dublin</geogname>. Louis Asekoff
        (1939- ), poet and educator, currently coordinates the M.F.A. Program in Poetry at <corpname
          authfilenumber="Brooklyn_College" source="dbpedia">Brooklyn College</corpname>. His poems
        have appeared in many magazines, including <corpname authfilenumber="The_new_yorker"
          source="dbpedia"><emph render="italic">The New Yorker</emph></corpname>, <corpname
          authfilenumber="Poetry_magazine" source="dbpedia"><emph render="italic"
          >Poetry</emph></corpname>, <corpname authfilenumber="Tikkun_(magazine)" source="dbpedia"
            ><emph render="italic">Tikkun</emph></corpname>, <corpname
          authfilenumber="Salmagundi_(magazine)" source="dbpedia"><emph render="italic"
            >Salmagundi</emph></corpname>, <corpname authfilenumber="Triquarterly" source="dbpedia"
            ><emph render="italic">Triquarterly</emph></corpname>, and <corpname
          authfilenumber="American_Poetry_Review" source="dbpedia"><emph render="italic">American
            Poetry Review</emph></corpname>. He has twice received The American Poetry Review Jerome
        Shestack Prize for Poetry. He has published two books of poetry, <title>Dreams of a
          Work</title> (1994) and <title>North Star</title> (1997) by Orchieses Press, <geogname
          authfilenumber="Washington,_D.C." source="dbpedia">Washington, D.C.</geogname> He has
        received poetry fellowships from the <corpname
          authfilenumber="National_Endowment_for_the_Arts" source="dbpedia">National Endowment for
          the Arts</corpname>, the <corpname authfilenumber="New_York_Foundation_for_the_Arts"
          source="dbpedia">New York Foundation for the Arts</corpname>, and The Fund for Poetry.</p>
    </bioghist>
    <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
      <head>Scope and Content Note</head>
      <p>The collection consists of letters and postcards from Derek Mahon to <persname
          authfilenumber="9071711" source="viaf">Louis Asekoff</persname> from 1963-1988 and
        reflects their close literary and personal friendship which began when both were students at
          <corpname authfilenumber="Trinity_College,_Dublin" source="dbpedia">Trinity College,
          Dublin</corpname> in the early sixties. Mahon's letters include references to poets and
        poetry, literary ambitions, teaching plans, reading tours, personal relationships, and
        visits with Asekoff. The collection also includes typscripts of several of Mahon's
        poems.</p>
    </scopecontent>
